      <h3>
        What is this project about?
      </h3>
      <p>
        Evanston residents love their trees. That's why when the Emerald Ash Borer started to claim the lives of thousands of our park and parkway ash trees over the past few years, we banded together and took action. It started with a few tree-knowledgeable volunteers helping the City maintain some of our current park trees through mulching and removing invasive plant species, such as buckthorn. As interest spread, the City started the "I Heart Evanston Trees" project in order begin a larger discussion about the threats facing our tree population and potential solutions.  
      <p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="big_wrapper">
  <div class="wrapper" id="two">
